 Mumbai (PTI): Allowing tax exemptions to Sachin Tendulkar and Sunil Gavaskar were a mistake and the income-tax department would take corrective measures soon, N.B. Singh, chief commissioner of income-tax (Mumbai), said on Wednesday.

 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court will on Thursday pronounce its verdict on the Centres demand for referring to a larger bench the OBC quota controversy. A bench headed by justice Arijit Pasayat had on May 9 asked the parties to the dispute to formulate their questions that can be considered by a larger bench.

 Kuala Lumpur (PTI): Malaysia is looking to recruit workers from neighbouring countries and India to meet its rising demand for maids, a report has said. The government will penalise recruitment agencies if maids, who are mostly from Indonesia, run away from their employers.

 New Delhi (PTI): Cable operators charging more than the amount prescribed for providing the CAS service will face cancellation of their licences, information and broadcasting minister Priya Ranjan Das Munshi told the Rajya Sabha on Wednesday. 

 New Delhi (PTI): The government has said religious headcount in the armed forces should not be permitted as it would affect its secular character. It was not desirable to supply such data as this would affect the ethos and cohesiveness of the forces, defence minister A.K. Antony said in Parliament.




